<title>USA: World Bank approves $400 mln China water project.</title>
<headline>World Bank approves $400 mln China water project.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1997-06-03</dateline>
<text>
<p>The World Bank on Tuesday approved a $400 million loan to assist in a project to transfer water from China's Yellow River to the Fen River.</p>
<p>The $1.35 billion project will use a system of tunnels, aqueducts and reservoirs to alleviate water shortages around the city of Taiyuan in Shanxi province in northeastern China, the World Bank said.</p>
<p>The loan will be at the bank's standard interest rate for LIBOR-based U.S. dollar, single-currency loans, with a maturity of 20 years, including a five-year grace period.</p>
